cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.NE, cs.DM, cs.GR 

The paper deals with image analysis and correction methods for serial section microscopy, which involves imaging biological specimens in thin sections. This falls under the domain of computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.MM) as the authors use image-based signal analysis to correct distortions in the image volumes. The application of these methods is in the field of neuroscience (cs.NE) for reconstruction of neural connectivity. The paper also involves graph theory (cs.DM) for ordering the section series and visualization (cs.GR) of the corrected image volumes.
